gtest_mpi
------------------------------------------
This project provides an extension to the Google Test framework, to allow
testing of MPI enabled applications. The implementation includes a custom MPI
environment and listener, with which all test failure messages are collected
on the root process and the output includes the rank index for each failure.

Runtime requirements:
  cygwin-3.6.9-1
  libgcc1-14.4.0-1
  libgtest0-1.17.0-1bl1
  libgtest_mpi-devel-2.0.0-1bl1
  libgtest_mpi2-2.0.0-1bl1
  libopenmpi40-4.1.6-1
  libstdc++6-14.4.0-1
  pkg-config-2.5.1-1

Build requirements:
(besides corresponding -devel packages)
  binutils-2.46.1-1
  cmake-4.2.1-1
  cygport-0.37.7-1
  gcc-core-14.4.0-1
  gcc-g++-14.4.0-1
  libgtest-devel-1.17.0-1bl1
  libopenmpi-devel-4.1.6-1
  ninja-1.13.2-1

Canonical website:
  https://github.com/AdhocMan/gtest_mpi

Canonical download:
  https://github.com/AdhocMan/gtest_mpi/archive/refs/tags/v2.0.0.tar.gz

-------------------------------------------

Build instructions:
  1. unpack gtest_mpi-2.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  2. if you use setup to install this src package,
     it will be unpacked under /usr/src automatically
        % cd /usr/src
        % cygport ./gtest_mpi-2.0.0-X.cygport all

This will create:
  /usr/src/gtest_mpi-2.0.0-X-src.tar.xz
  /usr/src/gtest_mpi-2.0.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libgtest_mpi2-2.0.0-X.tar.xz
  /usr/src/libgtest_mpi-devel-2.0.0-X.tar.xz

-------------------------------------------

Files included in the binary package:

(gtest_mpi)
  /usr/share/doc/Cygwin/gtest_mpi.README
  /usr/share/doc/gtest_mpi/LICENSE
  /usr/share/doc/gtest_mpi/README.md

(libgtest_mpi2)
  /usr/bin/cyggtest_mpi-2.dll

(libgtest_mpi-devel)
  /usr/include/gtest_mpi/gtest_mpi.hpp
  /usr/lib/cmake/gtest_mpi/gtest_mpi-config.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/gtest_mpi/gtest_mpi-targets-release.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/gtest_mpi/gtest_mpi-targets.cmake
  /usr/lib/cmake/gtest_mpi/gtest_mpi-version.cmake
  /usr/lib/libgtest_mpi.dll.a
  /usr/lib/pkgconfig/gtest_mpi.pc

